        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIG. 4. — Buziniphilus antiquus n. gen., n. sp., holotype: A, dorsolateral view of pedigerous trunk segments III-VII, including leg VI; B, ventrolateral view of trunk segments XVII-XIX; C, terminal part of trunk, ventral view (see Figure 3A for labelled drawing); D, left leg XL, posterior side; E, trunk segments XL-XLI, dorsal view. Abbreviations: f, femur; mc, metacoxa; ms, metasternum; mt, metatergum; pc, procoxa; pf, praefemur; ps, praesternum; pt, praetergum; tr, trochanter. Scale bars: A-D, 100 μm; E, 50 μm." ;
