        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIG. 2. — Buziniphilus antiquus n. gen., n. sp., holotype: A, dorsolateral view of head and anterior part of trunk; B, detail of scutes on anterior part of cephalic plate; C, ventrolateral view of head; D, tarsus and claw of left telopodite of second maxillae; E, ventral view of distal part of left forcipula; arrow indicates distal end of poison calyx. Abbreviations: cl, claw; fp, pleurite of forcipular segment; ft, tergum of forcipular segment; h, hinge between trochanteropraefemur and tarsungulum of forcipula; mt2, metatergum of second pedigerous segment; mx2, left telopodite of second maxillae; pt2, praetergum of second pedigerous segment; st, stigmatiferous sclerite; t1, tergum of first pedigerous segment; ta, tarsus. Scale bars: A, C, 100 μm; B, D, E, 20 μm." ;
